apes=3D"Picture_x0020_2"><![endif]><span
  lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>Gas Giants are s</span>upe=
r-size,
  Jupiter-like planets composed primarily of gases. They are the primary su=
pply
  of the two main fuel resources: Caslon and Hydrogen.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Their upper atmospheres are often ravaged by turbule=
nt
  storm winds that leave trails of swirling gas in their wake. Gas Giant
  planets are often orbited by a number of moons, some of which may be
  colonizable.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'=
>However
  Gas Giant planets themselves </span>cannot be colonized.<span lang=3DEN-GB
